## 1. Product intent (target state)

### 1.1 Primary use cases

| Phase | User need | System behavior |
|-------|-----------|-----------------|
| **Prep** | Build playbook before the call | Ingest PDFs, decks, CRM fields, prior notes → structured KB → MEDDPICC/SPIN gaps, talk tracks, objection matrix |
| **Live** | Stay aligned during call/demo | Streaming STT → intent + framework stage → prioritized coaching (not parallel unrelated analyses) |
| **Post** | Debrief & next steps | Summarize against framework coverage; CRM-ready outputs |

### 1.2 Sales methodologies to embed (non-exhaustive)

- **MEDDPICC / MEDDIC** — Metrics, Economic buyer, Decision criteria/process, Paper process, Implicate pain, Champion, Competition (variants exist; normalize to one schema in product).
- **SPIN** — Situation, Problem, Implication, Need-payoff.
- **Challenger / Command of the Message** — Commercial insight, reframe, rational drowning — optional modules.

The **current codebase is interview-centric** (tactical HUD: MOTIVE, DELIVERY, THE MOVE, RESCUE). Sales expansion requires **parallel framework schemas**, **stage detection**, and **non-blocking orchestration** so analysis never “chokes” live guidance.

