## 2. Current backend inventory (Next.js App Router)

All routes live under `web/app/api/`. Runtime: **Node** on the Next server; **no separate worker service**, **no message queue**, **no shared Redis** in-repo.

### 2.1 Route map

| Route | Method | Purpose | LLM | Streaming |
|-------|--------|---------|-----|-----------|
| `/api/token` | POST | Short-lived AssemblyAI token for browser WebSocket STT | No | JSON |
| `/api/copilot` | POST | Main tactical copilot; SSE token stream | Cohere **or** Groq (`LLM_PROVIDER`) | SSE |
| `/api/profiler` | POST | Behavioral “profiler”; merges JSON delta into `profilerState` | Same provider pattern | No |
| `/api/generate-context` | POST | From pasted JD/context → STT `keyterms` + `prompt` | Same | No |
| `/api/followup` | POST | Post-session markdown brief | Same | SSE |
| `/api/translate` | POST | Translation proxy (legacy/alternate pipeline) | External | Varies |

**Note:** If additional experiments added `/api/context` or similar locally, treat them as **optional** unless committed — agents should verify `web/app/api/` with `glob` before documenting dependencies.

### 2.2 Environment variables (typical)

- `ASSEMBLYAI_API_KEY` — Required for `/api/token`. **Must be set in deployment**; do not rely on any fallback in source.
- `COHERE_API_KEY` / `GROQ_API_KEY` — Depending on `LLM_PROVIDER`.
- `COHERE_MODEL`, `GROQ_MODEL` — Optional overrides.
- `LLM_PROVIDER` — `cohere` | `groq` (and potentially extended).

### 2.3 Knowledge base

- File: `web/lib/knowledge_base.json`
- Loaded synchronously in routes via `readFileSync` + `JSON.parse`.
- Used by copilot, profiler, follow-up prompts (`buildSystemPrompt.js` and related).

### 2.4 Prompt router (conceptual)

- `web/lib/buildSystemPrompt.js` centralizes system prompts (profiler, tactical variants, terminal/coding mode, follow-up).
- `/api/copilot` selects **one** system prompt per request based on `speaker`, `terminalMode`, `profilerState.conversation_phase`, and `clientTelemetry` flags (e.g. rescue, code-write).

