## 3. End-to-end data flow (today)

```
Browser mic/system audio
    → AssemblyAI WebSocket (token from POST /api/token)
    → Client hooks accumulate turns / gates firing
    → POST /api/copilot { text, speaker, history, profilerState, clipboardCode, terminalMode, clientTelemetry }
    → Single LLM stream (SSE) → UI parses tagged text ([MOTIVE], [RESCUE], …)

Parallel (often): every ~60s POST /api/profiler with transcript chunk → merges JSON into profilerState → fed into next copilot call.
```

**Critical characteristic:** The **dominant path is one LLM completing one long formatted string**. That is fundamentally why the product **“just dumps text”** and why **competing concerns** (profiler digest vs live tactical line vs framework checklist) **fight for the same latency budget and UI surface**.

---

## 4. Observed failure modes (“choking”)

These align with real transcripts (e.g. domain-heavy dialogue + sudden “write the code” / mode swings):

### 4.1 Single hot path

- One streaming completion carries **reasoning + tags + bullets**. Frontend strips hidden blocks (e.g. `<THINK>`) while streaming; any stall or malformed tag boundary reads as “stuck” or empty visible output.

### 4.2 Uncoordinated background work

- Profiler runs on a **wall-clock interval**, not on **semantic idle** or **framework milestones**. Copilot may fire **before** profiler insights land → inconsistent “phase” and mismatched coaching.

### 4.3 History compaction

- Client sends **truncated / normalized** history (`history` shaped as turns). Middle context loss produces **topic drift** (e.g. established thread forgotten when the prompt window is wrong).

### 4.4 Mode thrash

- Modes ([RESCUE], [STRENGTHEN], course correct, coding) are **re-derived each turn** from prompt + partial transcript. Partial clauses look like “freeze” → unnecessary rescue. Explicit buyer questions (“Can you write the code?”) arrive late → abrupt pivots.

### 4.5 No orchestration contract

- There is **no job queue**, **no priorities**, **no cancellation semantics** between “analyze last 60s” vs “answer immediate buyer objection”. Everything is **best-effort fetch** from the UI.

### 4.6 Single-model bottleneck

- Same provider/path used for **cheap classification** (could be small/fast) and **heavy generation**. No routing by task cost/latency/reliability.

